As a separate post said, I have started reading the Forgotten Realms book.  I have read up a bit about prestige classes and had a few questions...<P>First, why would someone want to remain a mage when they could become an arch mage?  What is the DISadvantage of being a prestige class?<P>Second (and I admit, this might answer the first question), do you get a multiclassing penalty if you are in a prestige class?<P>-Banyan (asking on behalf of Whitt, his level 6 gnome sorcerer)
