not sure banyan if becoming a prestige class incurrs the multiclass penalty.<BR>but if your main class is allowable by your race then there should be no problems. but if you raise a prestige class that does not count as your main class, so going to archmage 1 still means you are a 3rd level sorcerer / 1st level archmage<P>also you need to meet requirements first before becoming prestige classes. some of the ones for clerics state that you must have 13 ranks in religon before you can become one. so take a look for those, there usually is one.  right now i am playing a cleric/contimplative class<P>Kinda cool you playing what you playing, hope it works out for yas<P>Omc
