<HR size="1" color="#3299CC">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
the disadvantages of being a prestige class are quite light in some cases. It hurts warrior classes more than the caster types in general, but not always.<p>For instance take your Archmage vs straight mage.<p>Assuming that you still get spell progression as a wizard, you lose some of the saves that you would get as being a straight mage and you would miss out on the bonus feats you get for being a wizard.<p>Same with clerics, a prestige class cleric's turning power is no where near as good a straight clerics. And if you have seen the Defenders of the Faith handbook that can be good enough reason to stay a straight cleric.
<br>
