 | <a href="javascript:ce_enforce('26','000013','000004');">Problem??</a>
  </FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#3299CC">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
You get a 20% exp penalty for each class you have with more then a 1 level difference.<p>So if your a 1st level fighter, 2nd level cleric you have no penalty... (cause they are not more then 1 level apart)<br />If your a 1st level fighter, 3rd level cleric you have a 20% penalty... (20% for having more then one level from fighter to cleric)<br />If your a 1st fighter, 2nd rogue and 3rd cleric you have a 40% (20% for fighter/cleric, 20% for rogue/cleric but nothing from fighter/rogue since they are not more then 1 apart)<br />(One more...)<br />If your a 1st level fighter, 3rd rogue and a 5th cleric you suffer a 60% penalty (20% for fighter/cleric, 20% for rogue/cleric and 20% for fighter/rogue).<p>So make sure you never get a 6 classes to level 1 then work one of them up to level 3 without raising the others (20%X5 gives you a 100% penalty).  Hmm...  Wonder what happens if you get more then 6 before you raise one...<p><br />Each race has a preferred class (humans are whichever class is highest).  When figuring out level differences you do not count either your preferred class (since your race is good at that class) or prestige classes (since it would be unfair to make you gain 5 levels in a class to be able to take another only to give you a 20% penalty for it).<p>I don't know the specifics on the Forgotten Realms ones (only have the ones from DMG, Fist and Sword, Tome and Blood and Manual of the Plains) so I can't help out much there.  I do know that several in Tome and Blood don't get a caster level at every level though (I think only one or two in there do, the rest get one every other level or every two levels).  It should say under the class when its advanced.<p>Main disadvantage to being a prestige class is the requirements to become the class.  If you want to get there as early as you can then your first 3 to 8 levels are spent doing nothing but working on getting the prerequisites (some of those mage ones are killer).<br /><br />--------------------<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48842" target="_blank">Dalion Sleepstonight</a><br />level 30 paladin of Tunare</p>
